data.title: Great Restaurant
data.text: I love this place, parrillada is excellent and price are reasonable, I have a 1 year old and they accommodate him always. I love the services, desserts are delicious.

data.title: Great Parrillada
data.text: Friendly service, family friendly relaxed atmosphere.  Food was delicious and the serving sizes were huge. Try the mar y tierra!

data.title: Manager not trained enough...
data.text:
I just friendly wanted to share this information with the ownership...

FLORIDA – A WINEDOGGYBAG STATE – Endorsed by Florida Restaurant and Lodging Association
Section 564.09 of the Florida statutes provides that a restaurant licensed to sell wine may permit a patron to remove one unsealed bottle of wine if (i) the patron consumed a portion of the wine with the purchase of a full meal, (ii) the restaurant securely reseals the bottle, (iii) the bottle is placed in a bag that is secured in a manner that is visibly apparent if the bag has been opened and (iv) a dated receipt for the wine and meal is available.

As a hospitality worker I have learned through the years how important it is no to say NO to the guest. Specially when you're staff is not well informed. Thanks.

data.title: Great Menu with a variety of delicious food.
data.text: The staff are very welcoming and accommodating.  My husband picked this restaurant because the menu has such a wide variety including Argentinian and Italian.  We thoroughly enjoyed our meal together and look forward to coming back.

data.title: if you like argentinan food
data.text: if you like Argentinean cuisine and don't want to spend a fortune this is the place , parking is difficult some times in the front but usually there is no problem in the back

data.title: A piece of Argentina in Miami
data.text: As an Argentinian tourist in Miami I can assure you that Kussifay is like being in a typical "parrilla" in Buenos Aires.  It may be somewhat more gourmet ( logically,  since it is in Miami)  but still, the essence,  the meals served,  the atmosphere,  corresponds to any restaurant in Buenos Aires.  Do go if you are into trying new dishes without willing to do 8.000 km.

data.title: Excellent place to end our one month long holiday in Hollywood
data.text: Nice place.  The food and service was very good. We had a couple of Pina Colada to start which were very tasty. We will need to return this restaurant next year.

data.title: Not so hot!!!
data.text: Went for lunch. Food that we got was not so good. I got the steak sandwich which I ordered medium and it came over done. The meat was tough and I had to eat it with a fork and knife. The service was not very good neither. Our waitress was the only one there so that might have been the problem. Regardless, I don't think we'll be back.

data.title: Great food, really good service. Cute place
data.text: We had 6 adults that went for lunch on the way to our cruise in Miami. The ladies were very friendly and provided good fast service. They brought a bread basket  - really yummy! Two in our party ordered calzones. They were huge! They could have just shared one. Two more ordered entree salads with steak. They looked great! My husband and I shared a chicken parmesan plate, which was huge also. It had ham & cheese on the chicken, and not too much red sauce, which is the way I like it. We had fries, which everyone loved! Great lunch all around. Would go again when in town.

data.title: Like home
data.text: Amazing place, everyone make ur feel like family and the food is amazing, great fusion on Argentinian, Italian and American food. 100% recommended

data.title: Excellent food and service!!
data.text: The food is outstanding! Its fresh, great prices for what you get! HIGHLY recommend eating here!  The waitstaff is beyond personable and nice:} what a nice change. Empanadas are the BEST I have ever had! The chicken and mushrooms is to die for sangria is excellent all a round a great place for everything highly highly recommend!

data.title: Finally a real Argentinian
data.text: I was looking for a real Argentinian restaurant for 2 years since I came to Florida. Not fancy but nice and if you go to the bigger one in downtown it has space and the best Argentinian food in south Florida at a very good price

data.title: Didn't like the empanadas at all
data.text: We had eaten empanadas once before, maybe not Argentine style. Those were half moons, possibly fried, filled with juicy chicken chunks, veggies, and sauce. Delicious. But the ones I got here at Kussifay were awful. Small, plain, filled with very salty shredded chicken, beef, or spinach, period.

data.title: Excellent
data.text: Wonderful service, delicious food, energized atmosphere. Planning on visiting again 2015. We visited both locations. Tasty empanadas!

data.title: Sandwich from Heaven!
data.text: I had a sandwich that was recommended to me by the waitress....it had meat, ham, cheese and egg on it.  It was crazy good and the thin fries made the experience perfect!  My friends had some meat platter that was enough for two to share.  Yum!  Did I tell me my sandwich was big enough for two?  So yummy and economical!  The atmosphere is a little deceiving as it is nothing special but the food makes up for that!  Its also right off of I95 on Hollywood Blvd (east) so it is a good quick bite stop as you are passing by!

data.title: Great argentinean parrillada
data.text: best Argentinean parrillada in south florida I ever tried, and the price is the least expensive around and the quality is the best, bread is also excellent, and the same goes for dulce de leche ice cream, service very good too, my daughter loves this place and I do too.

data.title: Tasty Argentinian food
data.text:
Bread was amazing - warm and soft with a cheesy top - you don't need the butter but go ahead and have it anyway. Delicious. We could have just had this and left well fed and happy. 

The meal portions were huge!  I had a delicious fish dish. We prefer vegetables a bit crispier but I believe they were done in an authentic manner. 

The server was friendly, attentive and helpful. We sat at a table outside and people watched. A lovely evening.

data.title: Simplicity with excellent quality
data.text: Kussifay has become my almost everyday restaurant to go, The owner Gianina is present there most of the time making sure that the service and food quality is top in the area, beside her being a charming and sweetheart person by always welcoming me is an add on to her operation. The menu is a real Argentine expression of the normal food that is consumed in Argentina and the quality of it is excellent. Keep going Gianina !!

data.title: Great place!
data.text:
Went there several times with family and friends, place its small and usually very busy.
Food is very good, from the meat to the pizza, I tried most likely all, my favorite is milanesa napolitana and the Fuggazzeta rellena, which is a pizza with onions on top and filled with mozzarella and ham, its GREAT! Order that pizza and pair it with a cold Quilmes beer, you will love it! 
They serve big portions in most of the plates so if you are not a big eater you can easily share.

data.title: Amazing!!!!
data.text: If I can give 10 stars I will. The food is incredibly delicious. We came one day ended up coming for three days straight after our first time visit. Service 10 stars, food/ drinks 10 stars,and environment 10 stars. Definitely for parents on vacation with their children. Our server was considerate of our 9 month old baby and he was very professional. This place cares about their  customers and their satisfaction. Definitely recommend this place.
